
# for selections sorts:

Array = []

Outer Loops:

set how many times the inner loop must run. (run n-1)

Inner Loops:

finds the lowest value,
moves it to the front of the array
Loop must loop through one less value each time it runs.
    
# bubble sorts:

outer loops: An outer loop that controls how many times the inner loop must run.

Inner Loops:

goes through the array,
swaps values if the first value is higher than the next value.
This loop must loop through one less value each time it runs.